				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Unlike the NES, the Super NES uses VRAM in the console. All pixels have to be pushed to the console using DMA during vertical blanking. An ordinary 160x144 pixel frame at 2 bits per pixel is 5760 bytes, which is near the 6 KiB/frame practical cart-to-VRAM transfer speed that I've read for the NTSC Super NES.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
